The paper describes an autonomous bidding agent that won a trading competition by building a stochastic model of market prices and using a stochastic optimization technique to solve for an optimal set of bids. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to game theory (cs.GT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), multi-agent systems (cs.MA), and data structures (cs.DS).
